{
  "name": "posthog__remote-mcp",
  "display_name": "PostHog",
  "icon": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
  "description": "Remote MCP server for PostHog - product analytics, feature flags, experiments, error tracking, session replay, and LLM observability",
  "homepage": "https://posthog.com",
  "instructions": "⚠️ **Data region**: PostHog runs regional Cloud endpoints — US: `https://mcp.posthog.com/mcp`, EU: `https://mcp-eu.posthog.com/mcp`. With OAuth, PostHog automatically routes you to the correct region based on the account you sign in with, so the default URL works for both regions. If you authenticate with a personal API key and your organization is on EU Cloud, change the Server URL to `https://mcp-eu.posthog.com/mcp`.\n\n⚠️ **AI-powered tools** (sentiment analysis, trace summarization, etc.) only appear when AI data processing is enabled in your PostHog organization settings, and their usage may be billed as PostHog AI spend.\n\n## Authentication\n\n1. **OAuth (recommended)** — works out of the box: the server supports dynamic client registration, so no client ID or secret is needed. Sign in to PostHog in the browser and grant the per-product scopes you want (dashboards, insights, feature flags, experiments, error tracking, ...).\n2. **Personal API key (alternative)** — if your client can't do OAuth, create a personal API key with the **MCP Server** preset (it scopes access to a specific project) and send it as an `Authorization: Bearer phx_...` header.\n\n## Useful options (headers or query parameters)\n\n- `?readonly=true` — hide all tools that create, update, or delete data.\n- `?features=flags,dashboards,insights` — expose only specific product areas.\n- `x-posthog-organization-id` / `x-posthog-project-id` headers (or `organization_id` / `project_id` query parameters) — pin the session to one organization or project.\n- `x-posthog-mcp-mode` (`cli` or `tools`) — in CLI mode (the default for most clients) the server ships a single token-optimized `exec` tool instead of registering hundreds of tools; `tools` mode registers every tool individually.\n\nDocs: https://posthog.com/docs/model-context-protocol",
